[normal]The Financial Backdrop[bold]&#xa0;
[normal]26
[normal]              
[normal]              
[normal]The Commission has, like most govern
[normal]ment organisations, experienced
[normal] budget reductions in recent years. In the five years 
[normal]to
[normal] 2012/13, our
[normal] 
[normal]normal cash budget
[normal] 
[normal](
[normal]fiscal 
[normal]DEL
[normal] budget
[normal]) has reduced by more than 13.5
[normal]%.  Compensating for inflation, the reduction is almost 23%.  However, 
[normal]we are pleased to report that 
[normal]our
[normal] 2013/14 
[normal]budget
[normal] 
[normal]increased slightly
[normal]. A
[normal]fter taking out one-off costs incurred in 2012/13
[normal],
[normal] and factoring in additional savings made, this
[normal] allow
[normal]ed
[normal] us to recruit 
[normal]staff
[normal] to
[normal] help
[normal] deal with
[normal] rising business volumes
[normal].  
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]27
[normal]              
[normal]              
[normal]The budget reductions in the previous five years amou
[normal]nted to £0.8m in money terms
[normal] 
[normal](
[normal]£1.5m expres
[normal]sed in 
[normal]today’s money
[normal])
[normal].  
[normal]To
[normal] 
[normal]cope with these cuts 
[normal]we 
[normal]implemented e
[normal]fficiencies and cost savings.  As staff costs account for 
[normal]more than 
[normal]85% of our budget, significant savings had to come from reducing staff costs. A combination of a recruitment freeze and 
[normal]redundancies
[normal] 
[normal]reduced our case
[normal]working staff over this period from 56.5 FTE
[normal] to 46.9 FTE (a 17% reduction).
[normal] Our current year
[normal] budget
[normal] has enabled us to increase our casework staff complement back to 53.9 FTE average for the year to date.  The use of additional short contract staff 
[normal]should bring the
[normal] total up to about 60 FTE for the whole year.
