[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]Conclusion[bold]&#xa0;[bold]64
[normal]              
[normal]              
[normal]The Commission 
[normal]has proved its value in the criminal justice system over the last 16 years
[normal]. While 
[normal]we 
[normal]are grateful for the modest funding 
[normal]increase in 2013/14, 
[normal]particularly in light of the current economic climate, 
[normal]we are acutely aware that 
[normal]maintain
[normal]in
[normal]g 
[normal]at least the same 
[normal]level of fundi
[normal]n
[normal]g
[normal] for
[normal] 
[normal]next year will be 
[normal]cr
[normal]ucial to 
[normal]our ability 
[normal]to
[normal] 
[normal]deal 
[normal]properly 
[normal]with
[normal] the sustained increase in applications
[normal]. Only an increase in funding would allow us to reduce queues to more reasonable levels. 
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]65
[normal]              
[normal]              
[normal]We believe that our casework function and its support services are as lean as they can be and our ability to investigate cases and reach the appropria
[normal]te decision in each is as good now as it has ever been.
[normal] 
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]66
[normal]              
[normal]              
[normal]We are proud of and committed to our efforts to ensure that we 
[normal]remain independent and
[normal] accessible to all who need us. 
[normal]&#xa0;
