[normal] 
[normal]Custody cases are applications to the Commission from people in custody. 
[normal]Liberty
[normal] applications are applications from people who are at liberty.
[normal] 
[normal]The C
[normal]ommission
[normal] is essentially a post-appeal organisation and applicants usually need to have appealed, or at least sought leave to appeal, before the Commission can review their case. In some cases, where there are exceptional circumstances, the C
[normal]ommission c
[normal]an review a case in the absence of a prior attempt to appeal.
